Package: fastTextR
Type: Package
Title: Efficient learning of word representations and sentence classification using fastText in R
Version: 1.0.0
Author: Lampros Mouselimis <mouselimislampros@gmail.com>
Maintainer: Lampros Mouselimis <mouselimislampros@gmail.com>
BugReports: https://github.com/mlampros/fastTextR/issues
URL: https://github.com/mlampros/fastTextR
Description: The fastTextR package is a wrapper for the skipgram and cbow functions of the fastText (https://github.com/facebookresearch/fastText) library. fastText is a library for efficient learning of word representations and sentence classification. Since it uses C++11 features, it requires a compiler with good C++11 support. These include : (gcc-4.6.3 or newer) or (clang-3.3 or newer). More information about the fastText library can be found in https://github.com/facebookresearch/fastText.
License: GPL-3 + (COPYRIGHTS, LICENSE, PATENTS)
Copyright: inst/COPYRIGHTS
LazyData: TRUE
Depends:
    R(>= 3.2.3)
Imports:
    Rcpp (>= 0.12.5)
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo (>= 0.7.2)
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Suggests: covr
